title: Man-Cave | Watch: The funniest moment of the Rugby World Cup so far went down last night
text:
If you missed the France versus Canada Rugby World Cup game last night, you may have missed one of the funniest moments of the tournament so far.
Having held up considerably well in the first half against heavyweights France, Canada were trailing by a mere five points with three minutes left on the clock before half time with a lineout to France about 10m from the Canada line.
So what did Canadian lock Jamie Cudmore do? Just stuck his head into the French huddle to eavesdrop on their plans.
Not amusing for the French, very amusing for everyone else.
It didn't help in the end though, as France went on to score a try from the lineout, ending the half 24 - 12 before finishing the game 41 - 18.
Jamie Cudmore eavesdrops on France huddle MAGIC MOMENTJamie Cudmore attempts to eavesdrop the French huddle during their match at #RWC2015 #FRAvCAN. Brave man
